  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2010-07-01",
    "date": "2010-09-01T20:39:24Z",
    "text": "Predatory Lending Sunset Act - Amends the Truth in Lending Act to limit the maximum interest rate which a creditor may charge on a covered consumer credit loan of up to $3,000 to an annual percentage rate (APR) of 36%.\n\nProhibits a creditor from extending a covered loan with respect to which the creditor uses as security either: (1) access to a borrower's financial account; or (2) the title of a vehicle.\n\nAmends the Electronic Fund Transfer Act to prohibit a remotely created check that: (1) is not created by the financial institution that holds the customer account from which the check is to be paid; and (2) does not bear a signature applied by the person from whose account the check is to be paid.\n\nDeclares unenforceable, with respect to any consumer, any contract made in violation of this Act."
  },
